c Pigeonhole: 3 pigeons into 2 holes — classic small UNSAT instance.
c Variables: x_{i,j} = pigeon i is in hole j, encoded as (i-1)*2 + j for i in 1..3, j in 1..2
c   x_{1,1}=1  x_{1,2}=2
c   x_{2,1}=3  x_{2,2}=4
c   x_{3,1}=5  x_{3,2}=6
c Each pigeon must be in some hole: (x_{i,1} ∨ x_{i,2}) for i = 1..3
c No two pigeons share a hole: ¬x_{i,j} ∨ ¬x_{k,j} for i<k, j = 1..2
c Good stress test: all clauses have size 2, so no unit-clause branch is taken.
p cnf 6 9
1 2 0
3 4 0
5 6 0
-1 -3 0
-1 -5 0
-3 -5 0
-2 -4 0
-2 -6 0
-4 -6 0